%% Sankey / Data Flow example (use sankey-beta if Mermaid supports, else architecture-beta approximation).
%% ⚠️ If using architecture-beta alt below: same rule as three-layer — render-pipeline only. For .md source use weighted flowchart edges or sankey-beta when safe in your previewer.
%% Brief: Weighted flows for data transformation or resource movement.
%% Dials: Complexity 4, Density 4, Restraint 8.
%% Sankey specifics: Thicker lines for volume, semantic labels on edges, color by category, legend.
%% Mermaid sankey-beta syntax (if available in your Mermaid version):
sankey-beta
    Input [100] --> Process A
    Input --> Process B
    Process A [60] --> Output
    Process B [40] --> Output
    Waste [20] --> Discard

%% Alternative using architecture-beta for compatibility (groups as stages, edges with weights):
architecture-beta
    group input(database)[Input Stage]
    service raw[Raw Data 100] in input

    group process(cloud)[Processing]
    service a[Process A 60] in process
    service b[Process B 40] in process

    group output(database)[Output Stage]
    service final[Final Output 80] in output
    service waste[Waste 20] in output

    raw --> a
    raw --> b
    a --> final
    b --> final
    a --> waste
    b --> waste

    classDef stage fill:#f5f0eb,stroke:#002FA7,color:#1B365D
    class input,process,output stage

%% ASCII fallback for terminal: Vertical flow with width indicators.
%% Input (100)
%%   |==60==> Process A
%%   |==40==> Process B
%% Output (80)   Discard (20)
%% Use = for volume, --> for direction. Align for readability.